  {
    "Id": "135435",
    "ThreadId": "40688",
    "Html": "Hi,<br>\r\n<br>\r\nHere is a little example:<br>\r\n<br>\r\n&lt;dg:DataGrid Name=&quot;dataGrid&quot; Loaded=&quot;dataGrid_Loaded&quot; ItemsSource=&quot;{Binding}&quot; AutoGenerateColumns=&quot;False&quot; SelectionMode=&quot;Extended&quot;&gt;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;dg:DataGrid.Columns&gt;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;dg:DataGridComboBoxColumn x:Name=&quot;MyComboColumn&quot; Header=&quot;Type&quot; Width=&quot;60&quot; SelectedItemBinding=&quot;{Binding Path=Name}&quot;/&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &lt;/dg:DataGrid.Columns&gt;<br>\r\n&lt;/dg:DataGrid&gt;<br>\r\n<br>\r\nThe ComboBox column is given a x:Name, this enables us to locate it within the visual tree. We handle the Loaded event for the DataGrid, this occurs when the visual tree of the DataGrid is initially constructed.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWithin the event handler we can locate our column then set the ItemsSource programmatically:<br>\r\n<br>\r\nprivate void dataGrid_Loaded(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)<br>\r\n{<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DataGrid grid = sender as DataGrid;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; DataGridComboBoxColumn comboBoxColumn = grid.FindName(&quot;MyComboColumn&quot;) as DataGridComboBoxColumn;<br>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; comboBoxColumn.ItemsSource = new List&lt;string&gt;() { &quot;one&quot;, &quot;two&quot;, &quot;three&quot; };<br>\r\n}<br>\r\n<br>\r\nHope that helps,<br>\r\nColin E. <br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n",
    "PostedDate": "2008-11-26T01:03:12.28-08:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  }
